A Bottle and A Note<br>
-------------------------------------------------------------------<br>
<br>
Nospiratus stood by the desk staring at the bottle and the note. A bottle and a note.<br>
<br>
He had raised his hands several times to touch the smooth texture of the glass, but each time, he stopped as if a barrier had sprung forth between himself and the thing he desired. The note lay open faced upon the desk and he had read it and smiled, appreciating the thoughtfulness of the newly installed Dread Lord, his friend from the earliest days when the Harvest wore violet. He knew who the gift was from, but he still could not bring himself to touch it, much less consume its cold contents.<br>
<br>
Once more he reached forward, and again, the vision of a bottle of swirling mist touched his mind. After the visions of the previous night he was so tired...too tired to welcome one while awake. Then he sighed. If a vision ust come this morning, he knew he would have to accept it. These were dnagerous times, and he would not let fear and exhaustion stand in the way of his duty to the Harvest. Turning to the side of the desk, he pulled on the dangling purple cord. THere was no answering chime, for the summons was set to sound in a remote part of the city. His scribe would need a bonus, he thought for a moment. While he waited, he penned an order for rare sweet meats and a new slave to be sent to the address of a little known merchant in the foreign quarter. He would seethat it reached the proper place.<br>
<br>
After several moments, the cowled figure of his confidant entered the room and dutifully sat upon the lone stool in the corner, removing his vellum and quill from his worn cedar box. At last, he looked up to Nospiratus with bloodshot eyes and nodded.<br>
<br>
Without delay, like the swimmer jumping into ice cold water before the heat of the sun had touched its surface, he gripped the bottle.<br>
<br>
...to be continued...<br>
